  - Separate Dev, Test (UAT) and Live environments — we build and try changes safely, the testing team validates, then
  it goes live. A single switch configures each, so a change can't accidentally hit the live system.
  - Secure login — only authorized users get in (token-based); passwords are never stored or written to logs; the live
  system refuses to start if it's set up insecurely.
  - Solid, standard engineering — the code was reorganized into an industry-standard structure so the team can work on
  it safely and onboard quickly, with 80 automated tests confirming nothing breaks.
  - Full activity tracking + a monitoring dashboard — every action is recorded, viewable on a live dashboard, and the
  system automatically alerts the team if a serious error happens — so problems are caught and fixed fast, not
  discovered by users.
  - Clean error handling — users see friendly messages; engineers get the full technical detail behind the scenes.
  - Self-managing logs — records are searchable by a tracking ID and rotate automatically so files never grow out of
  control.
